Fix init.rs baking the permissive `dontAsk` default into new projects

`init.rs::STARTER_CLAW_JSON` (line 4) was the per-project counterpart
to the repo-level `dontAsk` default that patch 0001 fixed in
`.claude.json` and `rust/.claw.json`. Without this patch, every fresh
`claw init` would still write a `.claw.json` with
`"defaultMode": "dontAsk"`, which `runtime/config.rs:858` resolves to
`ResolvedPermissionMode::DangerFullAccess` — i.e. tools fire without
prompts in any newly-initialised project, defeating the hardening
done in 0001.

Replace the starter config with the same verified-working pattern
that's now in the repo's own `.claude.json` / `rust/.claw.json`:

  - `defaultMode: "default"` (resolves to `ReadOnly` — safe baseline)
  - `deny: [bash(curl:*), bash(wget:*), bash(sudo:*), bash(rm:*)]`
    (hard-block exfil + privilege-escalation + filesystem destruction)
  - `ask: [bash]` (catch-all prompt for anything else)

Update the `initialize_repo_writes_starter_files_and_claude_md` test
fixture (`init.rs:412`) to match the new expected output. All 179
`rusty-claude-cli` bin tests pass after the change; full workspace
suite (956 tests) also green.

The case-fix from patch 0005 (`Bash` → `bash`) is already correct in
this patch since the new entries use the lowercase form that matches
`mvp_tool_specs` (`tools/lib.rs:388`).
---
diff --git a/rust/crates/rusty-claude-cli/src/init.rs b/rust/crates/rusty-claude-cli/src/init.rs
--- a/rust/crates/rusty-claude-cli/src/init.rs
+++ b/rust/crates/rusty-claude-cli/src/init.rs
@@ -4,7 +4,16 @@
 const STARTER_CLAW_JSON: &str = concat!(
     "{\n",
     "  \"permissions\": {\n",
-    "    \"defaultMode\": \"dontAsk\"\n",
+    "    \"defaultMode\": \"default\",\n",
+    "    \"deny\": [\n",
+    "      \"bash(curl:*)\",\n",
+    "      \"bash(wget:*)\",\n",
+    "      \"bash(sudo:*)\",\n",
+    "      \"bash(rm:*)\"\n",
+    "    ],\n",
+    "    \"ask\": [\n",
+    "      \"bash\"\n",
+    "    ]\n",
     "  }\n",
     "}\n",
 );
@@ -409,7 +418,16 @@
             concat!(
